<TITLE> Bangladesh to play three one-day warm-up matches in New Zealand </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh will play three one-day warm-up matches before taking on New Zealand in the opener of three-ODI series on December 26 at Eden Park in Auckland. Bangladesh will also play a Twenty20 match against a New Zealand XI in between warm-up and one day internationals on December 22 at Seddon Park, Hamilton, but they will not get any warm-up matches before a two-Test series against the Kiwis. The first two warm-up matches against the Northern Districts will be held on Dec 16 and 18 in Hamilton while the last one against Auckland is billed for Dec 21. Bangladesh will take on the Black Caps in the first ODI on Dec 26 at Eden Park while the second will be held at McLean Park, Napier, on Dec 28. Queenstown will host the final ODI on Dec 31 before the first Test starts on January 4 at University Oval, Dunedin. Wellington will host the second and final Test from January 12 to 16. 
